e="preserve">Fambaré Ouattara Natchaba (17 April 1945 – 15 October 2020) was a Togolese politician. He was the President of the National Assembly of Togo from September 2000 to February 2005. He was a member of the Rally of the Togolese People (RPT). From 1994 to 2007, he was a member of the National Assembly. From 1992 to 1994, he was Minister of Foreign Affairs.
Natchaba died on 15 October 2020 at the age of 75.
